    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "a82f4b4ac6589b61",
      "text": "> codefrau 06/06/2022 — \nNo, you cannot directly interact with a world inside a portal currently, because of the way iframe event handling works. We could facilitate it via the outer shell which is able to forward messages between iframes. At the moment we keep this \"meta\" protocol to the absolutely necessary minimum – pretty much the only thing sent from the upper frame to a lower frame is the camera transform. Plus when entering a portal, the avatar data gets transmitted to the new world."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "53f39dde4953315f",
      "text": "> croqueteer 06/08/2022 —\nWe can't interact with worlds on the other side of portals at the moment, though we could. But, you really shouldn't (usually). We removed external control in the original Croquet because I felt it was an inappropriate action - especially if someone else was inside that world seeing a disembodied action occur."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "044806943a38fc1b",
      "text": "These architects make clear that there are good reasons to limit how much is expected to change hands between worlds. The aside, \"when entering a portal, the avatar data gets transmitted to the new world\", suggests that there is an established path."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "f5b887d006252602",
